    var style = JSON.parse(getStyle());
    args.apistyle = getEncodedStyles(style);
    return args;
}
function getEncodedStyles(styles) {
    var ret = &quot;&quot;;
    var styleparse_types = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;0&quot;,
        &quot;administrative&quot;: &quot;1&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.country&quot;: &quot;17&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.land_parcel&quot;: &quot;21&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.locality&quot;: &quot;19&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.neighborhood&quot;: &quot;20&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.province&quot;: &quot;18&quot;,
        &quot;landscape&quot;: &quot;5&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.man_made&quot;: &quot;81&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.natural&quot;: &quot;82&quot;,
        &quot;poi&quot;: &quot;2&quot;,
        &quot;poi.attraction&quot;: &quot;37&quot;,
        &quot;poi.business&quot;: &quot;33&quot;,
        &quot;poi.government&quot;: &quot;34&quot;,
        &quot;poi.medical&quot;: &quot;36&quot;,
        &quot;poi.park&quot;: &quot;40&quot;,
        &quot;poi.place_of_worship&quot;: &quot;38&quot;,
        &quot;poi.school&quot;: &quot;35&quot;,
        &quot;poi.sports_complex&quot;: &quot;39&quot;,
        &quot;road&quot;: &quot;3&quot;,
        &quot;road.arterial&quot;: &quot;50&quot;,
        &quot;road.highway&quot;: &quot;49&quot;,
        &quot;road.local&quot;: &quot;51&quot;,
        &quot;transit&quot;: &quot;4&quot;,
        &quot;transit.line&quot;: &quot;65&quot;,
        &quot;transit.station&quot;: &quot;66&quot;,
        &quot;water&quot;: &quot;6&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_elements = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;a&quot;,
        &quot;geometry&quot;: &quot;g&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.fill&quot;: &quot;g.f&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.stroke&quot;: &quot;g.s&quot;,
        &quot;labels&quot;: &quot;l&quot;,
        &quot;labels.icon&quot;: &quot;l.i&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text&quot;: &quot;l.t&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.fill&quot;: &quot;l.t.f&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.stroke&quot;: &quot;l.t.s&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_stylers = {
        &quot;color&quot;: &quot;p.c&quot;,
        &quot;gamma&quot;: &quot;p.g&quot;,
        &quot;hue&quot;: &quot;p.h&quot;,
        &quot;invert_lightness&quot;: &quot;p.il&quot;,
        &quot;lightness&quot;: &quot;p.l&quot;,
        &quot;saturation&quot;: &quot;p.s&quot;,
        &quot;visibility&quot;: &quot;p.v&quot;,
        &quot;weight&quot;: &quot;p.w&quot;
    };
    for (i = 0; i &amp;lt; styles.length; i++) {
        if (styles[i].featureType) {
            ret += &quot;s.t:&quot; + styleparse_types[styles[i].featureType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].elementType) {
            if (!styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType]) console.log(&quot;style element transcription unkown:&quot; + styles[i].elementType);
            ret += &quot;s.e:&quot; + styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].stylers) {
            for (u = 0; u &amp;lt; styles[i].stylers.length; u++) {
                var keys = [];
                var cstyler = styles[i].stylers[u]
                for (var k in cstyler) {
                    if (k == &quot;color&quot;) {
                        if (cstyler[k].length == 7) cstyler[k] = &quot;#ff&quot; + cstyler[k].slice(1);
                        else if (cstyler[k].length != 9) console.log(&quot;malformed color:&quot; + cstyler[k]);
                    }
                    ret += styleparse_stylers[k] + &quot;:&quot; + cstyler[k] + &quot;|&quot;;
                }
            }
        }
        ret = ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1);
        ret += &quot;,&quot;
    }
    return encodeURIComponent(ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1));
}','Visible','{&quot;BackgroundColor&quot;:&quot;&quot;}',NULL,'1','1');

    args.tilesize = &quot;512&quot;;
    args.dateFormat = getDate();
    args.nearestHour = getNearestHour();

}

function getDate(){
    var date = new Date();
    return date.getFullYear() + &quot;-&quot; +((date.getMonth()+1).length != 2 ? &quot;0&quot; + (date.getMonth() + 1) : (date.getMonth()+1)) + &quot;-&quot; + (date.getDate().length != 2 ?&quot;0&quot; + date.getDate() : date.getDate());
}
    
    function getNearestHour() {
  const hours = [0, 3, 6, 9, 12, 15, 18, 21];
  const currentHour = new Date().getUTCHours();
  let nearestHour = hours[0];

  for (let i = 1; i &amp;lt; hours.length; i++) {
    if (currentHour &amp;gt;= hours[i]) {
      nearestHour = hours[i];
    } else {
      break;
    }
  }

  return nearestHour.toString().padStart(2, &apos;0&apos;);
}

    let TargetSpatialReferenceWkt = &apos;PROJCS[&quot;WGS 84 / Pseudo-Mercator&quot;, GEOGCS[&quot;WGS 84&quot;, DATUM[&quot;World Geodetic System 1984&quot;, SPHEROID[&quot;WGS 84&quot;, 6378137, 298.257223563, AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;7030&quot;]], AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;6326&quot;]], PRIMEM[&quot;Greenwich&quot;, 0, AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;8901&quot;]], UNIT[&quot;degree&quot;, 0.017453292519943295, AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;9102&quot;]], AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;4326&quot;]], UNIT[&quot;metre&quot;, 1, AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;9001&quot;]], PROJECTION[&quot;Popular Visualisation Pseudo-Mercator&quot;, AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;3856&quot;]], PARAMETER[&quot;latitude_of_origin&quot;, 0], PARAMETER[&quot;central_meridian&quot;, 0], PARAMETER[&quot;false_easting&quot;, 0], PARAMETER[&quot;false_northing&quot;, 0], AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;3857&quot;], AXIS[&quot;East&quot;, EAST], AXIS[&quot;North&quot;, NORTH]]&apos;;
    let topBBox = transformLocationFromWGS84(TargetSpatialReferenceWkt, args.t_lng, args.t_lat);
    let botBBox = transformLocationFromWGS84(TargetSpatialReferenceWkt, args.b_lng, args.b_lat);
    args.bbox = topBBox[0] + &quot;,&quot; + botBBox[1] + &quot;,&quot; + botBBox[0] + &quot;,&quot; + topBBox[1];
    args.tilesize = &quot;512&quot;;
    args.dateFormat = getDate();
    args.nearestHour = getNearestHour();
    return args;
}

function getDate(){
    var date = new Date();
    return date.getFullYear() + &quot;-&quot; +((date.getMonth()+1).length != 2 ? &quot;0&quot; + (date.getMonth() + 1) : (date.getMonth()+1)) + &quot;-&quot; + (date.getDate().length != 2 ?&quot;0&quot; + date.getDate() : date.getDate());
}
    
    function getNearestHour() {
  const hours = [0, 3, 6, 9, 12, 15, 18, 21];
  const currentHour = new Date().getUTCHours();
  let nearestHour = hours[0];

  for (let i = 1; i &amp;lt; hours.length; i++) {
    if (currentHour &amp;gt;= hours[i]) {
      nearestHour = hours[i];
    } else {
      break;
    }
  }

  return nearestHour.toString().padStart(2, &apos;0&apos;);
}

function getDate(){
    var date = new Date();
    return date.getFullYear() + &quot;-&quot; +((date.getMonth()+1).length != 2 ? &quot;0&quot; + (date.getMonth() + 1) : (date.getMonth()+1)) + &quot;-&quot; + (date.getDate().length != 2 ?&quot;0&quot; + date.getDate() : date.getDate());
}
    
    function getNearestHour() {
  const hours = [0, 3, 6, 9, 12, 15, 18, 21];
  const currentHour = new Date().getUTCHours();
  let nearestHour = hours[0];

  for (let i = 1; i &amp;lt; hours.length; i++) {
    if (currentHour &amp;gt;= hours[i]) {
      nearestHour = hours[i];
    } else {
      break;
    }
  }

  return nearestHour.toString().padStart(2, &apos;0&apos;);
}

Ces &eacute;l&eacute;ments de d&eacute;limitation maritime sont issus des limites calcul&eacute;es par le Shom sur la base du droit international, des accords de d&eacute;limitation maritime et conventions ratifi&eacute;s entre deux Etats, des d&eacute;cisions d’une instance juridique internationale, des recommandations de la Commission des limites du plateau continental de l’ONU ou encore de revendication de d&eacute;limitation unilat&eacute;rale de la France en l’absence d’accord. Un DST est un syst&egrave;me d’organisation du trafic visant &agrave; s&eacute;parer des flux de trafic oppos&eacute;s par des moyens appropri&eacute;s et notamment par l’&eacute;tablissement de couloirs de circulation. 
Les mesures prises visent &agrave; am&eacute;liorer la s&eacute;curit&eacute; de la navigation dans les zones o&ugrave; celle-ci est menac&eacute;e par la densit&eacute; du trafic associ&eacute;e &agrave; des difficult&eacute;s naturelles diverses. Plusieurs classes d’objets composent ce produit, les acronymes utilis&eacute;s sont ceux de la norme S-57 de l’OHI : 
- Couloirs de circulation (TSSLPT) : sections &agrave; l&apos;int&eacute;rieur desquelles le trafic se fait suivant une direction &eacute;tablie ; 
- Limites de dispositif de s&eacute;paration du trafic (TSSBND) : limites ext&eacute;rieures d&apos;un couloir de circulation ou d&apos;un rond-point de dispositif de s&eacute;paration du trafic ; 
- Lignes de s&eacute;paration du trafic (TSELNE) : lignes de s&eacute;paration entre deux couloirs de circulation ou entre un couloir de circulation et une zone de navigation c&ocirc;ti&egrave;re ; 
- Zones de s&eacute;paration du trafic (TSEZNE) : zones de s&eacute;paration entre deux couloirs de circulation ou entre un couloir de circulation et une zone de navigation c&ocirc;ti&egrave;re ou encore zone centrale d&apos;un rond-point ; - Zones de navigation c&ocirc;ti&egrave;re (ISTZNE) : zones situ&eacute;es entre la limite c&ocirc;t&eacute; terre d&apos;un dispositif de s&eacute;paration de trafic et la c&ocirc;te ; 
- Zones de prudence (PRCARE) : zones dont les limites sont d&eacute;finies, o&ugrave; les navires doivent naviguer avec une attention particuli&egrave;re, et &agrave; l&apos;int&eacute;rieur desquelles la direction du trafic peut &ecirc;tre recommand&eacute;e ; - Sections de routes en eau profonde (DWRTPT) : sections &agrave; l&apos;int&eacute;rieur desquelles le trafic se fait soit suivant une direction &eacute;tablie pour un trafic &agrave; sens unique ou soit suivant une direction &eacute;tablie et celle oppos&eacute;e pour un trafic &agrave; double sens. Une route en eau profonde est une route r&eacute;glement&eacute;e, situ&eacute;e dans des limites d&eacute;termin&eacute;es, et qui a fait l&apos;objet de lev&eacute;s hydrographiques pr&eacute;cis permettant de garantir une certaine hauteur d&apos;eau au-dessus du fond et des objets immerg&eacute;s ; 
- Routes &agrave; double sens de circulation (TWRTPT) : sections &agrave; l&apos;int&eacute;rieur desquelles le trafic se fait suivant deux directions oppos&eacute;es le long d&apos;un rel&egrave;vement. Ces sections sont g&eacute;n&eacute;ralement &agrave; double sens, mais certaines peuvent &ecirc;tre &agrave; sens unique ; 
- Lignes d’appel radio (RDOCAL_lne) : positions o&ugrave; les navires sont tenus de contacter un centre de contr&ocirc;le du trafic.

function getDate(){
    var date = new Date();
    return date.getFullYear() + &quot;-&quot; +((date.getMonth()+1).length != 2 ? &quot;0&quot; + (date.getMonth() + 1) : (date.getMonth()+1)) + &quot;-&quot; + (date.getDate().length != 2 ?&quot;0&quot; + date.getDate() : date.getDate());
}
    
    function getNearestHour() {
  const hours = [0, 3, 6, 9, 12, 15, 18, 21];
  const currentHour = new Date().getUTCHours();
  let nearestHour = hours[0];

  for (let i = 1; i &amp;lt; hours.length; i++) {
    if (currentHour &amp;gt;= hours[i]) {
      nearestHour = hours[i];
    } else {
      break;
    }
  }

  return nearestHour.toString().padStart(2, &apos;0&apos;);
}

function getDate(){
    var date = new Date();
    return date.getFullYear() + &quot;-&quot; +((date.getMonth()+1).length != 2 ? &quot;0&quot; + (date.getMonth() + 1) : (date.getMonth()+1)) + &quot;-&quot; + (date.getDate().length != 2 ?&quot;0&quot; + date.getDate() : date.getDate());
}
    
    function getNearestHour() {
  const hours = [0, 3, 6, 9, 12, 15, 18, 21];
  const currentHour = new Date().getUTCHours();
  let nearestHour = hours[0];

  for (let i = 1; i &amp;lt; hours.length; i++) {
    if (currentHour &amp;gt;= hours[i]) {
      nearestHour = hours[i];
    } else {
      break;
    }
  }

  return nearestHour.toString().padStart(2, &apos;0&apos;);
}

function getDate(){
    var date = new Date();
    return date.getFullYear() + &quot;-&quot; +((date.getMonth()+1).length != 2 ? &quot;0&quot; + (date.getMonth() + 1) : (date.getMonth()+1)) + &quot;-&quot; + (date.getDate().length != 2 ?&quot;0&quot; + date.getDate() : date.getDate());
}
    
    function getNearestHour() {
  const hours = [0, 3, 6, 9, 12, 15, 18, 21];
  const currentHour = new Date().getUTCHours();
  let nearestHour = hours[0];

  for (let i = 1; i &amp;lt; hours.length; i++) {
    if (currentHour &amp;gt;= hours[i]) {
      nearestHour = hours[i];
    } else {
      break;
    }
  }

  return nearestHour.toString().padStart(2, &apos;0&apos;);
}

function getEncodedStyles(styles) {
    var ret = &quot;&quot;;
    var styleparse_types = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;0&quot;,
        &quot;administrative&quot;: &quot;1&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.country&quot;: &quot;17&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.land_parcel&quot;: &quot;21&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.locality&quot;: &quot;19&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.neighborhood&quot;: &quot;20&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.province&quot;: &quot;18&quot;,
        &quot;landscape&quot;: &quot;5&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.man_made&quot;: &quot;81&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.natural&quot;: &quot;82&quot;,
        &quot;poi&quot;: &quot;2&quot;,
        &quot;poi.attraction&quot;: &quot;37&quot;,
        &quot;poi.business&quot;: &quot;33&quot;,
        &quot;poi.government&quot;: &quot;34&quot;,
        &quot;poi.medical&quot;: &quot;36&quot;,
        &quot;poi.park&quot;: &quot;40&quot;,
        &quot;poi.place_of_worship&quot;: &quot;38&quot;,
        &quot;poi.school&quot;: &quot;35&quot;,
        &quot;poi.sports_complex&quot;: &quot;39&quot;,
        &quot;road&quot;: &quot;3&quot;,
        &quot;road.arterial&quot;: &quot;50&quot;,
        &quot;road.highway&quot;: &quot;49&quot;,
        &quot;road.local&quot;: &quot;51&quot;,
        &quot;transit&quot;: &quot;4&quot;,
        &quot;transit.line&quot;: &quot;65&quot;,
        &quot;transit.station&quot;: &quot;66&quot;,
        &quot;water&quot;: &quot;6&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_elements = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;a&quot;,
        &quot;geometry&quot;: &quot;g&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.fill&quot;: &quot;g.f&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.stroke&quot;: &quot;g.s&quot;,
        &quot;labels&quot;: &quot;l&quot;,
        &quot;labels.icon&quot;: &quot;l.i&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text&quot;: &quot;l.t&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.fill&quot;: &quot;l.t.f&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.stroke&quot;: &quot;l.t.s&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_stylers = {
        &quot;color&quot;: &quot;p.c&quot;,
        &quot;gamma&quot;: &quot;p.g&quot;,
        &quot;hue&quot;: &quot;p.h&quot;,
        &quot;invert_lightness&quot;: &quot;p.il&quot;,
        &quot;lightness&quot;: &quot;p.l&quot;,
        &quot;saturation&quot;: &quot;p.s&quot;,
        &quot;visibility&quot;: &quot;p.v&quot;,
        &quot;weight&quot;: &quot;p.w&quot;
    };
    for (i = 0; i &amp;lt; styles.length; i++) {
        if (styles[i].featureType) {
            ret += &quot;s.t:&quot; + styleparse_types[styles[i].featureType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].elementType) {
            if (!styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType]) console.log(&quot;style element transcription unkown:&quot; + styles[i].elementType);
            ret += &quot;s.e:&quot; + styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].stylers) {
            for (u = 0; u &amp;lt; styles[i].stylers.length; u++) {
                var keys = [];
                var cstyler = styles[i].stylers[u]
                for (var k in cstyler) {
                    if (k == &quot;color&quot;) {
                        if (cstyler[k].length == 7) cstyler[k] = &quot;#ff&quot; + cstyler[k].slice(1);
                        else if (cstyler[k].length != 9) console.log(&quot;malformed color:&quot; + cstyler[k]);
                    }
                    ret += styleparse_stylers[k] + &quot;:&quot; + cstyler[k] + &quot;|&quot;;
                }
            }
        }
        ret = ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1);
        ret += &quot;,&quot;
    }
    return encodeURIComponent(ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1));
}','Visible','{&quot;BackgroundColor&quot;:&quot;&quot;}',NULL,'1','1');

getTile(args) {
    var style = JSON.parse(getStyle());
    args.apistyle = getEncodedStyles(style);
    return args;
}
function getEncodedStyles(styles) {
    var ret = &quot;&quot;;
    var styleparse_types = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;0&quot;,
        &quot;administrative&quot;: &quot;1&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.country&quot;: &quot;17&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.land_parcel&quot;: &quot;21&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.locality&quot;: &quot;19&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.neighborhood&quot;: &quot;20&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.province&quot;: &quot;18&quot;,
        &quot;landscape&quot;: &quot;5&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.man_made&quot;: &quot;81&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.natural&quot;: &quot;82&quot;,
        &quot;poi&quot;: &quot;2&quot;,
        &quot;poi.attraction&quot;: &quot;37&quot;,
        &quot;poi.business&quot;: &quot;33&quot;,
        &quot;poi.government&quot;: &quot;34&quot;,
        &quot;poi.medical&quot;: &quot;36&quot;,
        &quot;poi.park&quot;: &quot;40&quot;,
        &quot;poi.place_of_worship&quot;: &quot;38&quot;,
        &quot;poi.school&quot;: &quot;35&quot;,
        &quot;poi.sports_complex&quot;: &quot;39&quot;,
        &quot;road&quot;: &quot;3&quot;,
        &quot;road.arterial&quot;: &quot;50&quot;,
        &quot;road.highway&quot;: &quot;49&quot;,
        &quot;road.local&quot;: &quot;51&quot;,
        &quot;transit&quot;: &quot;4&quot;,
        &quot;transit.line&quot;: &quot;65&quot;,
        &quot;transit.station&quot;: &quot;66&quot;,
        &quot;water&quot;: &quot;6&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_elements = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;a&quot;,
        &quot;geometry&quot;: &quot;g&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.fill&quot;: &quot;g.f&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.stroke&quot;: &quot;g.s&quot;,
        &quot;labels&quot;: &quot;l&quot;,
        &quot;labels.icon&quot;: &quot;l.i&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text&quot;: &quot;l.t&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.fill&quot;: &quot;l.t.f&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.stroke&quot;: &quot;l.t.s&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_stylers = {
        &quot;color&quot;: &quot;p.c&quot;,
        &quot;gamma&quot;: &quot;p.g&quot;,
        &quot;hue&quot;: &quot;p.h&quot;,
        &quot;invert_lightness&quot;: &quot;p.il&quot;,
        &quot;lightness&quot;: &quot;p.l&quot;,
        &quot;saturation&quot;: &quot;p.s&quot;,
        &quot;visibility&quot;: &quot;p.v&quot;,
        &quot;weight&quot;: &quot;p.w&quot;
    };
    for (i = 0; i &amp;lt; styles.length; i++) {
        if (styles[i].featureType) {
            ret += &quot;s.t:&quot; + styleparse_types[styles[i].featureType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].elementType) {
            if (!styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType]) console.log(&quot;style element transcription unkown:&quot; + styles[i].elementType);
            ret += &quot;s.e:&quot; + styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].stylers) {
            for (u = 0; u &amp;lt; styles[i].stylers.length; u++) {
                var keys = [];
                var cstyler = styles[i].stylers[u]
                for (var k in cstyler) {
                    if (k == &quot;color&quot;) {
                        if (cstyler[k].length == 7) cstyler[k] = &quot;#ff&quot; + cstyler[k].slice(1);
                        else if (cstyler[k].length != 9) console.log(&quot;malformed color:&quot; + cstyler[k]);
                    }
                    ret += styleparse_stylers[k] + &quot;:&quot; + cstyler[k] + &quot;|&quot;;
                }
            }
        }
        ret = ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1);
        ret += &quot;,&quot;
    }
    return encodeURIComponent(ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1));
}','Visible','{&quot;BackgroundColor&quot;:&quot;&quot;}',NULL,'1','1');

function getEncodedStyles(styles) {
    var ret = &quot;&quot;;
    var styleparse_types = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;0&quot;,
        &quot;administrative&quot;: &quot;1&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.country&quot;: &quot;17&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.land_parcel&quot;: &quot;21&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.locality&quot;: &quot;19&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.neighborhood&quot;: &quot;20&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.province&quot;: &quot;18&quot;,
        &quot;landscape&quot;: &quot;5&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.man_made&quot;: &quot;81&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.natural&quot;: &quot;82&quot;,
        &quot;poi&quot;: &quot;2&quot;,
        &quot;poi.attraction&quot;: &quot;37&quot;,
        &quot;poi.business&quot;: &quot;33&quot;,
        &quot;poi.government&quot;: &quot;34&quot;,
        &quot;poi.medical&quot;: &quot;36&quot;,
        &quot;poi.park&quot;: &quot;40&quot;,
        &quot;poi.place_of_worship&quot;: &quot;38&quot;,
        &quot;poi.school&quot;: &quot;35&quot;,
        &quot;poi.sports_complex&quot;: &quot;39&quot;,
        &quot;road&quot;: &quot;3&quot;,
        &quot;road.arterial&quot;: &quot;50&quot;,
        &quot;road.highway&quot;: &quot;49&quot;,
        &quot;road.local&quot;: &quot;51&quot;,
        &quot;transit&quot;: &quot;4&quot;,
        &quot;transit.line&quot;: &quot;65&quot;,
        &quot;transit.station&quot;: &quot;66&quot;,
        &quot;water&quot;: &quot;6&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_elements = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;a&quot;,
        &quot;geometry&quot;: &quot;g&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.fill&quot;: &quot;g.f&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.stroke&quot;: &quot;g.s&quot;,
        &quot;labels&quot;: &quot;l&quot;,
        &quot;labels.icon&quot;: &quot;l.i&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text&quot;: &quot;l.t&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.fill&quot;: &quot;l.t.f&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.stroke&quot;: &quot;l.t.s&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_stylers = {
        &quot;color&quot;: &quot;p.c&quot;,
        &quot;gamma&quot;: &quot;p.g&quot;,
        &quot;hue&quot;: &quot;p.h&quot;,
        &quot;invert_lightness&quot;: &quot;p.il&quot;,
        &quot;lightness&quot;: &quot;p.l&quot;,
        &quot;saturation&quot;: &quot;p.s&quot;,
        &quot;visibility&quot;: &quot;p.v&quot;,
        &quot;weight&quot;: &quot;p.w&quot;
    };
    for (i = 0; i &amp;lt; styles.length; i++) {
        if (styles[i].featureType) {
            ret += &quot;s.t:&quot; + styleparse_types[styles[i].featureType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].elementType) {
            if (!styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType]) console.log(&quot;style element transcription unkown:&quot; + styles[i].elementType);
            ret += &quot;s.e:&quot; + styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].stylers) {
            for (u = 0; u &amp;lt; styles[i].stylers.length; u++) {
                var keys = [];
                var cstyler = styles[i].stylers[u]
                for (var k in cstyler) {
                    if (k == &quot;color&quot;) {
                        if (cstyler[k].length == 7) cstyler[k] = &quot;#ff&quot; + cstyler[k].slice(1);
                        else if (cstyler[k].length != 9) console.log(&quot;malformed color:&quot; + cstyler[k]);
                    }
                    ret += styleparse_stylers[k] + &quot;:&quot; + cstyler[k] + &quot;|&quot;;
                }
            }
        }
        ret = ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1);
        ret += &quot;,&quot;
    }
    return encodeURIComponent(ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1));
}','Visible','{&quot;BackgroundColor&quot;:&quot;&quot;}',NULL,'1','1');

getTile(args) {
    var style = JSON.parse(getStyle());
    args.apistyle = getEncodedStyles(style);
    return args;

function getEncodedStyles(styles) {
    var ret = &quot;&quot;;
    var styleparse_types = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;0&quot;,
        &quot;administrative&quot;: &quot;1&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.country&quot;: &quot;17&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.land_parcel&quot;: &quot;21&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.locality&quot;: &quot;19&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.neighborhood&quot;: &quot;20&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.province&quot;: &quot;18&quot;,
        &quot;landscape&quot;: &quot;5&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.man_made&quot;: &quot;81&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.natural&quot;: &quot;82&quot;,
        &quot;poi&quot;: &quot;2&quot;,
        &quot;poi.attraction&quot;: &quot;37&quot;,
        &quot;poi.business&quot;: &quot;33&quot;,
        &quot;poi.government&quot;: &quot;34&quot;,
        &quot;poi.medical&quot;: &quot;36&quot;,
        &quot;poi.park&quot;: &quot;40&quot;,
        &quot;poi.place_of_worship&quot;: &quot;38&quot;,
        &quot;poi.school&quot;: &quot;35&quot;,
        &quot;poi.sports_complex&quot;: &quot;39&quot;,
        &quot;road&quot;: &quot;3&quot;,
        &quot;road.arterial&quot;: &quot;50&quot;,
        &quot;road.highway&quot;: &quot;49&quot;,
        &quot;road.local&quot;: &quot;51&quot;,
        &quot;transit&quot;: &quot;4&quot;,
        &quot;transit.line&quot;: &quot;65&quot;,
        &quot;transit.station&quot;: &quot;66&quot;,
        &quot;water&quot;: &quot;6&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_elements = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;a&quot;,
        &quot;geometry&quot;: &quot;g&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.fill&quot;: &quot;g.f&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.stroke&quot;: &quot;g.s&quot;,
        &quot;labels&quot;: &quot;l&quot;,
        &quot;labels.icon&quot;: &quot;l.i&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text&quot;: &quot;l.t&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.fill&quot;: &quot;l.t.f&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.stroke&quot;: &quot;l.t.s&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_stylers = {
        &quot;color&quot;: &quot;p.c&quot;,
        &quot;gamma&quot;: &quot;p.g&quot;,
        &quot;hue&quot;: &quot;p.h&quot;,
        &quot;invert_lightness&quot;: &quot;p.il&quot;,
        &quot;lightness&quot;: &quot;p.l&quot;,
        &quot;saturation&quot;: &quot;p.s&quot;,
        &quot;visibility&quot;: &quot;p.v&quot;,
        &quot;weight&quot;: &quot;p.w&quot;
    };
    for (i = 0; i &amp;lt; styles.length; i++) {
        if (styles[i].featureType) {
            ret += &quot;s.t:&quot; + styleparse_types[styles[i].featureType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].elementType) {
            if (!styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType]) console.log(&quot;style element transcription unkown:&quot; + styles[i].elementType);
            ret += &quot;s.e:&quot; + styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].stylers) {
            for (u = 0; u &amp;lt; styles[i].stylers.length; u++) {
                var keys = [];
                var cstyler = styles[i].stylers[u]
                for (var k in cstyler) {
                    if (k == &quot;color&quot;) {
                        if (cstyler[k].length == 7) cstyler[k] = &quot;#ff&quot; + cstyler[k].slice(1);
                        else if (cstyler[k].length != 9) console.log(&quot;malformed color:&quot; + cstyler[k]);
                    }
                    ret += styleparse_stylers[k] + &quot;:&quot; + cstyler[k] + &quot;|&quot;;
                }
            }
        }
        ret = ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1);
        ret += &quot;,&quot;
    }
    return encodeURIComponent(ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1));
}','Visible','{&quot;BackgroundColor&quot;:&quot;&quot;}',NULL,'1','1');

    var style = JSON.parse(getStyle());
    args.apistyle = getEncodedStyles(style);
    return args;
}
function getEncodedStyles(styles) {
    var ret = &quot;&quot;;
    var styleparse_types = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;0&quot;,
        &quot;administrative&quot;: &quot;1&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.country&quot;: &quot;17&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.land_parcel&quot;: &quot;21&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.locality&quot;: &quot;19&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.neighborhood&quot;: &quot;20&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.province&quot;: &quot;18&quot;,
        &quot;landscape&quot;: &quot;5&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.man_made&quot;: &quot;81&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.natural&quot;: &quot;82&quot;,
        &quot;poi&quot;: &quot;2&quot;,
        &quot;poi.attraction&quot;: &quot;37&quot;,
        &quot;poi.business&quot;: &quot;33&quot;,
        &quot;poi.government&quot;: &quot;34&quot;,
        &quot;poi.medical&quot;: &quot;36&quot;,
        &quot;poi.park&quot;: &quot;40&quot;,
        &quot;poi.place_of_worship&quot;: &quot;38&quot;,
        &quot;poi.school&quot;: &quot;35&quot;,
        &quot;poi.sports_complex&quot;: &quot;39&quot;,
        &quot;road&quot;: &quot;3&quot;,
        &quot;road.arterial&quot;: &quot;50&quot;,
        &quot;road.highway&quot;: &quot;49&quot;,
        &quot;road.local&quot;: &quot;51&quot;,
        &quot;transit&quot;: &quot;4&quot;,
        &quot;transit.line&quot;: &quot;65&quot;,
        &quot;transit.station&quot;: &quot;66&quot;,
        &quot;water&quot;: &quot;6&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_elements = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;a&quot;,
        &quot;geometry&quot;: &quot;g&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.fill&quot;: &quot;g.f&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.stroke&quot;: &quot;g.s&quot;,
        &quot;labels&quot;: &quot;l&quot;,
        &quot;labels.icon&quot;: &quot;l.i&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text&quot;: &quot;l.t&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.fill&quot;: &quot;l.t.f&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.stroke&quot;: &quot;l.t.s&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_stylers = {
        &quot;color&quot;: &quot;p.c&quot;,
        &quot;gamma&quot;: &quot;p.g&quot;,
        &quot;hue&quot;: &quot;p.h&quot;,
        &quot;invert_lightness&quot;: &quot;p.il&quot;,
        &quot;lightness&quot;: &quot;p.l&quot;,
        &quot;saturation&quot;: &quot;p.s&quot;,
        &quot;visibility&quot;: &quot;p.v&quot;,
        &quot;weight&quot;: &quot;p.w&quot;
    };
    for (i = 0; i &amp;lt; styles.length; i++) {
        if (styles[i].featureType) {
            ret += &quot;s.t:&quot; + styleparse_types[styles[i].featureType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].elementType) {
            if (!styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType]) console.log(&quot;style element transcription unkown:&quot; + styles[i].elementType);
            ret += &quot;s.e:&quot; + styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].stylers) {
            for (u = 0; u &amp;lt; styles[i].stylers.length; u++) {
                var keys = [];
                var cstyler = styles[i].stylers[u]
                for (var k in cstyler) {
                    if (k == &quot;color&quot;) {
                        if (cstyler[k].length == 7) cstyler[k] = &quot;#ff&quot; + cstyler[k].slice(1);
                        else if (cstyler[k].length != 9) console.log(&quot;malformed color:&quot; + cstyler[k]);
                    }
                    ret += styleparse_stylers[k] + &quot;:&quot; + cstyler[k] + &quot;|&quot;;
                }
            }
        }
        ret = ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1);
        ret += &quot;,&quot;
    }
    return encodeURIComponent(ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1));
}','Visible','{&quot;BackgroundColor&quot;:&quot;&quot;}',NULL,'1','1');

        &quot;transit.line&quot;: &quot;65&quot;,
        &quot;transit.station&quot;: &quot;66&quot;,
        &quot;water&quot;: &quot;6&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_elements = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;a&quot;,
        &quot;geometry&quot;: &quot;g&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.fill&quot;: &quot;g.f&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.stroke&quot;: &quot;g.s&quot;,
        &quot;labels&quot;: &quot;l&quot;,
        &quot;labels.icon&quot;: &quot;l.i&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text&quot;: &quot;l.t&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.fill&quot;: &quot;l.t.f&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.stroke&quot;: &quot;l.t.s&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_stylers = {
        &quot;color&quot;: &quot;p.c&quot;,
        &quot;gamma&quot;: &quot;p.g&quot;,
        &quot;hue&quot;: &quot;p.h&quot;,
        &quot;invert_lightness&quot;: &quot;p.il&quot;,
        &quot;lightness&quot;: &quot;p.l&quot;,
        &quot;saturation&quot;: &quot;p.s&quot;,
        &quot;visibility&quot;: &quot;p.v&quot;,
        &quot;weight&quot;: &quot;p.w&quot;
    };
    for (i = 0; i &amp;lt; styles.length; i++) {
        if (styles[i].featureType) {
            ret += &quot;s.t:&quot; + styleparse_types[styles[i].featureType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].elementType) {
            if (!styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType]) console.log(&quot;style element transcription unkown:&quot; + styles[i].elementType);
            ret += &quot;s.e:&quot; + styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].stylers) {
            for (u = 0; u &amp;lt; styles[i].stylers.length; u++) {
                var keys = [];
                var cstyler = styles[i].stylers[u]
                for (var k in cstyler) {
                    if (k == &quot;color&quot;) {
                        if (cstyler[k].length == 7) cstyler[k] = &quot;#ff&quot; + cstyler[k].slice(1);
                        else if (cstyler[k].length != 9) console.log(&quot;malformed color:&quot; + cstyler[k]);
                    }
                    ret += styleparse_stylers[k] + &quot;:&quot; + cstyler[k] + &quot;|&quot;;
                }
            }
        }
        ret = ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1);
        ret += &quot;,&quot;
    }
    return encodeURIComponent(ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1));
}','Visible','{&quot;BackgroundColor&quot;:&quot;&quot;}',NULL,'1','1');

                        if (cstyler[k].length == 7) cstyler[k] = &quot;#ff&quot; + cstyler[k].slice(1);

                    }
                    ret += styleparse_stylers[k] + &quot;:&quot; + cstyler[k] + &quot;|&quot;;
                }
            }
        }
        ret = ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1);
        ret += &quot;,&quot;
    }
    return encodeURIComponent(ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1));
}','Visible','{&quot;BackgroundColor&quot;:&quot;&quot;}',NULL,'1','1');

function getEncodedStyles(styles) {
    var ret = &quot;&quot;;
    var styleparse_types = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;0&quot;,
        &quot;administrative&quot;: &quot;1&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.country&quot;: &quot;17&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.land_parcel&quot;: &quot;21&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.locality&quot;: &quot;19&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.neighborhood&quot;: &quot;20&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.province&quot;: &quot;18&quot;,
        &quot;landscape&quot;: &quot;5&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.man_made&quot;: &quot;81&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.natural&quot;: &quot;82&quot;,
        &quot;poi&quot;: &quot;2&quot;,
        &quot;poi.attraction&quot;: &quot;37&quot;,
        &quot;poi.business&quot;: &quot;33&quot;,
        &quot;poi.government&quot;: &quot;34&quot;,
        &quot;poi.medical&quot;: &quot;36&quot;,
        &quot;poi.park&quot;: &quot;40&quot;,
        &quot;poi.place_of_worship&quot;: &quot;38&quot;,
        &quot;poi.school&quot;: &quot;35&quot;,
        &quot;poi.sports_complex&quot;: &quot;39&quot;,
        &quot;road&quot;: &quot;3&quot;,
        &quot;road.arterial&quot;: &quot;50&quot;,
        &quot;road.highway&quot;: &quot;49&quot;,
        &quot;road.local&quot;: &quot;51&quot;,
        &quot;transit&quot;: &quot;4&quot;,
        &quot;transit.line&quot;: &quot;65&quot;,
        &quot;transit.station&quot;: &quot;66&quot;,
        &quot;water&quot;: &quot;6&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_elements = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;a&quot;,
        &quot;geometry&quot;: &quot;g&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.fill&quot;: &quot;g.f&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.stroke&quot;: &quot;g.s&quot;,
        &quot;labels&quot;: &quot;l&quot;,
        &quot;labels.icon&quot;: &quot;l.i&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text&quot;: &quot;l.t&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.fill&quot;: &quot;l.t.f&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.stroke&quot;: &quot;l.t.s&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_stylers = {
        &quot;color&quot;: &quot;p.c&quot;,
        &quot;gamma&quot;: &quot;p.g&quot;,
        &quot;hue&quot;: &quot;p.h&quot;,
        &quot;invert_lightness&quot;: &quot;p.il&quot;,
        &quot;lightness&quot;: &quot;p.l&quot;,
        &quot;saturation&quot;: &quot;p.s&quot;,
        &quot;visibility&quot;: &quot;p.v&quot;,
        &quot;weight&quot;: &quot;p.w&quot;
    };
    for (i = 0; i &amp;lt; styles.length; i++) {
        if (styles[i].featureType) {
            ret += &quot;s.t:&quot; + styleparse_types[styles[i].featureType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].elementType) {
            if (!styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType]) console.log(&quot;style element transcription unkown:&quot; + styles[i].elementType);
            ret += &quot;s.e:&quot; + styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].stylers) {
            for (u = 0; u &amp;lt; styles[i].stylers.length; u++) {
                var keys = [];
                var cstyler = styles[i].stylers[u]
                for (var k in cstyler) {
                    if (k == &quot;color&quot;) {
                        if (cstyler[k].length == 7) cstyler[k] = &quot;#ff&quot; + cstyler[k].slice(1);
                        else if (cstyler[k].length != 9) console.log(&quot;malformed color:&quot; + cstyler[k]);
                    }
                    ret += styleparse_stylers[k] + &quot;:&quot; + cstyler[k] + &quot;|&quot;;
                }
            }
        }
        ret = ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1);
        ret += &quot;,&quot;
    }
    return encodeURIComponent(ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1));
}','Visible','{&quot;BackgroundColor&quot;:&quot;&quot;}',NULL,'1','1');

function getEncodedStyles(styles) {
    var ret = &quot;&quot;;
    var styleparse_types = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;0&quot;,
        &quot;administrative&quot;: &quot;1&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.country&quot;: &quot;17&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.land_parcel&quot;: &quot;21&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.locality&quot;: &quot;19&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.neighborhood&quot;: &quot;20&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.province&quot;: &quot;18&quot;,
        &quot;landscape&quot;: &quot;5&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.man_made&quot;: &quot;81&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.natural&quot;: &quot;82&quot;,
        &quot;poi&quot;: &quot;2&quot;,
        &quot;poi.attraction&quot;: &quot;37&quot;,
        &quot;poi.business&quot;: &quot;33&quot;,
        &quot;poi.government&quot;: &quot;34&quot;,
        &quot;poi.medical&quot;: &quot;36&quot;,
        &quot;poi.park&quot;: &quot;40&quot;,
        &quot;poi.place_of_worship&quot;: &quot;38&quot;,
        &quot;poi.school&quot;: &quot;35&quot;,
        &quot;poi.sports_complex&quot;: &quot;39&quot;,
        &quot;road&quot;: &quot;3&quot;,
        &quot;road.arterial&quot;: &quot;50&quot;,
        &quot;road.highway&quot;: &quot;49&quot;,
        &quot;road.local&quot;: &quot;51&quot;,
        &quot;transit&quot;: &quot;4&quot;,
        &quot;transit.line&quot;: &quot;65&quot;,
        &quot;transit.station&quot;: &quot;66&quot;,
        &quot;water&quot;: &quot;6&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_elements = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;a&quot;,
        &quot;geometry&quot;: &quot;g&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.fill&quot;: &quot;g.f&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.stroke&quot;: &quot;g.s&quot;,
        &quot;labels&quot;: &quot;l&quot;,
        &quot;labels.icon&quot;: &quot;l.i&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text&quot;: &quot;l.t&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.fill&quot;: &quot;l.t.f&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.stroke&quot;: &quot;l.t.s&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_stylers = {
        &quot;color&quot;: &quot;p.c&quot;,
        &quot;gamma&quot;: &quot;p.g&quot;,
        &quot;hue&quot;: &quot;p.h&quot;,
        &quot;invert_lightness&quot;: &quot;p.il&quot;,
        &quot;lightness&quot;: &quot;p.l&quot;,
        &quot;saturation&quot;: &quot;p.s&quot;,
        &quot;visibility&quot;: &quot;p.v&quot;,
        &quot;weight&quot;: &quot;p.w&quot;
    };
    for (i = 0; i &amp;lt; styles.length; i++) {
        if (styles[i].featureType) {
            ret += &quot;s.t:&quot; + styleparse_types[styles[i].featureType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].elementType) {
            if (!styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType]) console.log(&quot;style element transcription unkown:&quot; + styles[i].elementType);
            ret += &quot;s.e:&quot; + styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].stylers) {
            for (u = 0; u &amp;lt; styles[i].stylers.length; u++) {
                var keys = [];
                var cstyler = styles[i].stylers[u]
                for (var k in cstyler) {
                    if (k == &quot;color&quot;) {
                        if (cstyler[k].length == 7) cstyler[k] = &quot;#ff&quot; + cstyler[k].slice(1);
                        else if (cstyler[k].length != 9) console.log(&quot;malformed color:&quot; + cstyler[k]);
                    }
                    ret += styleparse_stylers[k] + &quot;:&quot; + cstyler[k] + &quot;|&quot;;
                }
            }
        }
        ret = ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1);
        ret += &quot;,&quot;
    }
    return encodeURIComponent(ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1));
}','Visible','{&quot;BackgroundColor&quot;:&quot;&quot;}',NULL,'1','1');

                    }
                    ret += styleparse_stylers[k] + &quot;:&quot; + cstyler[k] + &quot;|&quot;;
                }
            }
        }
        ret = ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1);
        ret += &quot;,&quot;
    }
    return encodeURIComponent(ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1));

function getEncodedStyles(styles) {
    var ret = &quot;&quot;;
    var styleparse_types = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;0&quot;,
        &quot;administrative&quot;: &quot;1&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.country&quot;: &quot;17&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.land_parcel&quot;: &quot;21&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.locality&quot;: &quot;19&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.neighborhood&quot;: &quot;20&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.province&quot;: &quot;18&quot;,
        &quot;landscape&quot;: &quot;5&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.man_made&quot;: &quot;81&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.natural&quot;: &quot;82&quot;,
        &quot;poi&quot;: &quot;2&quot;,
        &quot;poi.attraction&quot;: &quot;37&quot;,
        &quot;poi.business&quot;: &quot;33&quot;,
        &quot;poi.government&quot;: &quot;34&quot;,
        &quot;poi.medical&quot;: &quot;36&quot;,
        &quot;poi.park&quot;: &quot;40&quot;,
        &quot;poi.place_of_worship&quot;: &quot;38&quot;,
        &quot;poi.school&quot;: &quot;35&quot;,
        &quot;poi.sports_complex&quot;: &quot;39&quot;,
        &quot;road&quot;: &quot;3&quot;,
        &quot;road.arterial&quot;: &quot;50&quot;,
        &quot;road.highway&quot;: &quot;49&quot;,
        &quot;road.local&quot;: &quot;51&quot;,
        &quot;transit&quot;: &quot;4&quot;,
        &quot;transit.line&quot;: &quot;65&quot;,
        &quot;transit.station&quot;: &quot;66&quot;,
        &quot;water&quot;: &quot;6&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_elements = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;a&quot;,
        &quot;geometry&quot;: &quot;g&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.fill&quot;: &quot;g.f&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.stroke&quot;: &quot;g.s&quot;,
        &quot;labels&quot;: &quot;l&quot;,
        &quot;labels.icon&quot;: &quot;l.i&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text&quot;: &quot;l.t&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.fill&quot;: &quot;l.t.f&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.stroke&quot;: &quot;l.t.s&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_stylers = {
        &quot;color&quot;: &quot;p.c&quot;,
        &quot;gamma&quot;: &quot;p.g&quot;,
        &quot;hue&quot;: &quot;p.h&quot;,
        &quot;invert_lightness&quot;: &quot;p.il&quot;,
        &quot;lightness&quot;: &quot;p.l&quot;,
        &quot;saturation&quot;: &quot;p.s&quot;,
        &quot;visibility&quot;: &quot;p.v&quot;,
        &quot;weight&quot;: &quot;p.w&quot;
    };
    for (i = 0; i &amp;lt; styles.length; i++) {
        if (styles[i].featureType) {
            ret += &quot;s.t:&quot; + styleparse_types[styles[i].featureType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].elementType) {
            if (!styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType]) console.log(&quot;style element transcription unkown:&quot; + styles[i].elementType);
            ret += &quot;s.e:&quot; + styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].stylers) {
            for (u = 0; u &amp;lt; styles[i].stylers.length; u++) {
                var keys = [];
                var cstyler = styles[i].stylers[u]
                for (var k in cstyler) {
                    if (k == &quot;color&quot;) {
                        if (cstyler[k].length == 7) cstyler[k] = &quot;#ff&quot; + cstyler[k].slice(1);
                        else if (cstyler[k].length != 9) console.log(&quot;malformed color:&quot; + cstyler[k]);
                    }
                    ret += styleparse_stylers[k] + &quot;:&quot; + cstyler[k] + &quot;|&quot;;
                }
            }
        }
        ret = ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1);
        ret += &quot;,&quot;
    }
    return encodeURIComponent(ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1));
}','Visible','{&quot;BackgroundColor&quot;:&quot;&quot;}',NULL,'1','1');

getTile(args) {
    var style = JSON.parse(getStyle());
    args.apistyle = getEncodedStyles(style);
    return args;
}
function getEncodedStyles(styles) {
    var ret = &quot;&quot;;
    var styleparse_types = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;0&quot;,
        &quot;administrative&quot;: &quot;1&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.country&quot;: &quot;17&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.land_parcel&quot;: &quot;21&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.locality&quot;: &quot;19&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.neighborhood&quot;: &quot;20&quot;,
        &quot;administrative.province&quot;: &quot;18&quot;,
        &quot;landscape&quot;: &quot;5&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.man_made&quot;: &quot;81&quot;,
        &quot;landscape.natural&quot;: &quot;82&quot;,
        &quot;poi&quot;: &quot;2&quot;,
        &quot;poi.attraction&quot;: &quot;37&quot;,
        &quot;poi.business&quot;: &quot;33&quot;,
        &quot;poi.government&quot;: &quot;34&quot;,
        &quot;poi.medical&quot;: &quot;36&quot;,
        &quot;poi.park&quot;: &quot;40&quot;,
        &quot;poi.place_of_worship&quot;: &quot;38&quot;,
        &quot;poi.school&quot;: &quot;35&quot;,
        &quot;poi.sports_complex&quot;: &quot;39&quot;,
        &quot;road&quot;: &quot;3&quot;,
        &quot;road.arterial&quot;: &quot;50&quot;,
        &quot;road.highway&quot;: &quot;49&quot;,
        &quot;road.local&quot;: &quot;51&quot;,
        &quot;transit&quot;: &quot;4&quot;,
        &quot;transit.line&quot;: &quot;65&quot;,
        &quot;transit.station&quot;: &quot;66&quot;,
        &quot;water&quot;: &quot;6&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_elements = {
        &quot;all&quot;: &quot;a&quot;,
        &quot;geometry&quot;: &quot;g&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.fill&quot;: &quot;g.f&quot;,
        &quot;geometry.stroke&quot;: &quot;g.s&quot;,
        &quot;labels&quot;: &quot;l&quot;,
        &quot;labels.icon&quot;: &quot;l.i&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text&quot;: &quot;l.t&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.fill&quot;: &quot;l.t.f&quot;,
        &quot;labels.text.stroke&quot;: &quot;l.t.s&quot;
    };
    var styleparse_stylers = {
        &quot;color&quot;: &quot;p.c&quot;,
        &quot;gamma&quot;: &quot;p.g&quot;,
        &quot;hue&quot;: &quot;p.h&quot;,
        &quot;invert_lightness&quot;: &quot;p.il&quot;,
        &quot;lightness&quot;: &quot;p.l&quot;,
        &quot;saturation&quot;: &quot;p.s&quot;,
        &quot;visibility&quot;: &quot;p.v&quot;,
        &quot;weight&quot;: &quot;p.w&quot;
    };
    for (i = 0; i &amp;lt; styles.length; i++) {
        if (styles[i].featureType) {
            ret += &quot;s.t:&quot; + styleparse_types[styles[i].featureType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].elementType) {
            if (!styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType]) console.log(&quot;style element transcription unkown:&quot; + styles[i].elementType);
            ret += &quot;s.e:&quot; + styleparse_elements[styles[i].elementType] + &quot;|&quot;;
        }
        if (styles[i].stylers) {
            for (u = 0; u &amp;lt; styles[i].stylers.length; u++) {
                var keys = [];
                var cstyler = styles[i].stylers[u]
                for (var k in cstyler) {
                    if (k == &quot;color&quot;) {
                        if (cstyler[k].length == 7) cstyler[k] = &quot;#ff&quot; + cstyler[k].slice(1);
                        else if (cstyler[k].length != 9) console.log(&quot;malformed color:&quot; + cstyler[k]);
                    }
                    ret += styleparse_stylers[k] + &quot;:&quot; + cstyler[k] + &quot;|&quot;;
                }
            }
        }
        ret = ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1);
        ret += &quot;,&quot;
    }
    return encodeURIComponent(ret.slice(0, ret.length - 1));
}','Visible','{&quot;BackgroundColor&quot;:&quot;&quot;}',NULL,'1','1');

    let TargetSpatialReferenceWkt = &apos;PROJCS[&quot;WGS 84 / Pseudo-Mercator&quot;, GEOGCS[&quot;WGS 84&quot;, DATUM[&quot;World Geodetic System 1984&quot;, SPHEROID[&quot;WGS 84&quot;, 6378137, 298.257223563, AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;7030&quot;]], AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;6326&quot;]], PRIMEM[&quot;Greenwich&quot;, 0, AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;8901&quot;]], UNIT[&quot;degree&quot;, 0.017453292519943295, AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;9102&quot;]], AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;4326&quot;]], UNIT[&quot;metre&quot;, 1, AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;9001&quot;]], PROJECTION[&quot;Popular Visualisation Pseudo-Mercator&quot;, AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;3856&quot;]], PARAMETER[&quot;latitude_of_origin&quot;, 0], PARAMETER[&quot;central_meridian&quot;, 0], PARAMETER[&quot;false_easting&quot;, 0], PARAMETER[&quot;false_northing&quot;, 0], AUTHORITY[&quot;EPSG&quot;, &quot;3857&quot;], AXIS[&quot;East&quot;, EAST], AXIS[&quot;North&quot;, NORTH]]&apos;;
    let topBBox = transformLocationFromWGS84(TargetSpatialReferenceWkt, args.t_lng, args.t_lat);
    let botBBox = transformLocationFromWGS84(TargetSpatialReferenceWkt, args.b_lng, args.b_lat);
    args.bbox = topBBox[0] + &quot;,&quot; + topBBox[1] + &quot;,&quot; + botBBox[0] + &quot;,&quot; + botBBox[1];
    args.tilesize = &quot;512&quot;;
    args.layers = encodeURIComponent(&quot;show:2&quot;);
    return args;
}

function getTile(args) {
    args.quadkey = getQuadKey(args.x, args.y,args.z);
   return args;
}


function getQuadKey(x, y, z) {
    //alert(x + &quot; &quot; + y + &quot; &quot; + z)
        var quadKey = [];
        for (var i = z; i &amp;gt; 0; i--) {
            var digit = &apos;0&apos;;
            var mask = 1 &amp;lt;&amp;lt; (i - 1);
            if ((x &amp; mask) != 0) {
                digit++;
            }
            if ((y &amp; mask) != 0) {
                digit++;
                digit++;
            }
            quadKey.push(digit);
        }
        return quadKey.join(&apos;&apos;);
    }','Visible','{&quot;BackgroundColor&quot;:&quot;&quot;}',NULL,'1','1');

                digit++;
            }
            if ((y &amp; mask) != 0) {
                digit++;
                digit++;
            }
            quadKey.push(digit);
        }
        return quadKey.join(&apos;&apos;);
    }','Visible','{&quot;BackgroundColor&quot;:&quot;&quot;}',NULL,'1','1');

In addition to global satellite and terrain coverage, over the past several years we&apos;ve been adding highly detailed 3D imagery of entire cities and towns. You can see a map of these places here.     let heading = 0;
    sendNotif();
    return getAjustedLocation(args, heading);
}

function sendNotif(){
notification(&quot;Click here to set the reference point. Visit earth.google.com to see where 3D tiles are available.&quot;, &quot;Google Maps - Tilted View&quot;, &quot;changeRefPoint&quot;,&quot;changeRefPointNotif&quot;, false);
}

function changeRefPoint() {
    var MidView = getView()[&quot;MID&quot;];
    setVar(&quot;savedPoint&quot;, MidView, true);
    refreshMap();
    clearCache();
    sendNotif();
}

function getAjustedLocation(args, heading) {
    let refPoint = getVar(&quot;savedPoint&quot;);
    if (refPoint == null){
   refPoint= getView()[&quot;MID&quot;];
    }
    let deltaY = 0;
    let minZ = 14;
    let referenceTileNumber = getTileNumber(refPoint.lat, refPoint.lng, minZ);
    let deltaX = Math.round(getDelta(minZ, args.z, referenceTileNumber.x) - args.x);
    let deltaY = Math.round(getDelta(minZ, args.z, referenceTileNumber.y) - args.y);
    let referenceOblicTileNumber = convertToOblic(refPoint.lat, refPoint.lng, minZ, heading);
    let finalx = Math.round(getDelta(minZ, args.z, referenceOblicTileNumber.x) - deltaX);
    let finaly = Math.round(getDelta(minZ, args.z, referenceOblicTileNumber.y) - deltaY);
    let returnObject = new Object;
    returnObject.x = finalx.toString();
    returnObject.y = finaly.toString();
    returnObject.z = args.z.toString();
    returnObject.heading = heading.toString();
    return returnObject;
}
function convertToOblic(lat, lng, zoom, heading) {
    var WMProjPoint = WebMercatorProject(lat, lng, zoom);
    var OblWMProjPoint = OblicWebMercator(WMProjPoint.x, WMProjPoint.y, WMProjPoint.z, heading);
    return OblWMProjPoint;
}
function getDelta(minZ, searchZoom, refTileValue) {
    if (searchZoom &amp;lt;= minZ) {
        let diviseur = minZ - searchZoom;
        return refTileValue / Math.pow(2, diviseur);
    } else {
        let diviseur = searchZoom - minZ;
        return refTileValue * Math.pow(2, diviseur);
    }
}
function WebMercatorProject(lat, lon, zoom) {
    let factor = (1 / (2 * Math.PI)) * Math.pow(2, zoom);
    let x = factor * ((lon * (Math.PI / 180)) + Math.PI);
    let y = factor * (Math.PI - Math.log(Math.tan((Math.PI / 4) + ((lat * (Math.PI / 180)) / 2))));
    var returnTiles = new Object();
    returnTiles.x = x;
    returnTiles.y = y;
    returnTiles.z = zoom;
    return returnTiles;
}
function OblicWebMercator(x0, y0, zoom, heading) {
    let width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles = Math.pow(2, zoom);
    let equator_offset_from_edges = width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles / 2;
    let x = x0;
    let y = y0;
    if (heading == 0) { //is_northward
    }
    if (heading == 90) { //is_eastward
        x = y0;
        y = width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles - x0;
    }
    if (heading == 180) { //is_southward
        x = width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles - x0;
        y = width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles - y0;
    }
    if (heading == 270) { //is_westward
        x = width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles - y0;
        y = x0;
    }
    y = ((y - equator_offset_from_edges) / Math.sqrt(2)) + equator_offset_from_edges
    var returnTiles = new Object();
    returnTiles.x = Math.floor(x).toString();
    returnTiles.y = Math.floor(y).toString();
    returnTiles.z = zoom;
    returnTiles.heading = heading.toString();
    return returnTiles;
}

    args.x = &quot;4823&quot;;
    args.y = &quot;6755&quot;;
    args.z = &quot;14&quot;;
    args.heading = &quot;0&quot;;
    return args;

function getDelta(minZ, searchZoom, refTileValue) {

function WebMercatorProject(lat, lon, zoom) {
    let factor = 1 / (2 * Math.PI) * Math.pow(2, zoom);
    let x = factor * (lon * (Math.PI / 180) + Math.PI);
    let y = factor * (Math.PI - Math.log(Math.tan(Math.PI / 4 + lat * (Math.PI / 180) / 2)));
    var returnTiles = new Object;
    returnTiles.x = x;
    returnTiles.y = y;
    returnTiles.z = zoom;
    return returnTiles;
}
function OblicWebMercator(x0, y0, zoom, heading) {
    let width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles = Math.pow(2, zoom);
    let equator_offset_from_edges = width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles / 2;
    let x = x0;
    let y = y0;
    if (heading == 0) {}
    if (heading == 90) {
        x = y0;
        y = width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles - x0;
    }
    if (heading == 180) {
        x = width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles - x0;
        y = width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles - y0;
    }
    if (heading == 270) {
        x = width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles - y0;
        y = x0;
    }
    y = (y - equator_offset_from_edges) / Math.sqrt(2) + equator_offset_from_edges;
    var returnTiles = new Object;
    returnTiles.x = Math.floor(x).toString();
    returnTiles.y = Math.floor(y).toString();
    returnTiles.z = zoom;
    returnTiles.heading = heading.toString();
    return returnTiles;
}

In addition to global satellite and terrain coverage, over the past several years we&apos;ve been adding highly detailed 3D imagery of entire cities and towns. You can see a map of these places here.     let heading = 180;
    sendNotif();
    return getAjustedLocation(args, heading);
}

function sendNotif(){
notification(&quot;Click here to set the reference point&quot;, &quot;Google Maps - Tilted View&quot;, &quot;changeRefPoint&quot;,&quot;changeRefPointNotif&quot;, false);
}

function changeRefPoint() {
    var MidView = getView()[&quot;MID&quot;];
    setVar(&quot;savedPoint&quot;, MidView, true);
    refreshMap();
    sendNotif();
}

function getAjustedLocation(args, heading) {
    let refPoint = getVar(&quot;savedPoint&quot;);
    if (refPoint == null){
    refPoint = getView()[&quot;MID&quot;];
    }
    let deltaY = 0;
    let minZ = 14;
    let referenceTileNumber = getTileNumber(refPoint.lat, refPoint.lng, minZ);
    let deltaX = Math.round(getDelta(minZ, args.z, referenceTileNumber.x) - args.x);
    let deltaY = Math.round(getDelta(minZ, args.z, referenceTileNumber.y) - args.y);
    let referenceOblicTileNumber = convertToOblic(refPoint.lat, refPoint.lng, minZ, heading);
    let finalx = Math.round(getDelta(minZ, args.z, referenceOblicTileNumber.x) - deltaX);
    let finaly = Math.round(getDelta(minZ, args.z, referenceOblicTileNumber.y) - deltaY);
    let returnObject = new Object;
    returnObject.x = finalx.toString();
    returnObject.y = finaly.toString();
    returnObject.z = args.z.toString();
    returnObject.heading = heading.toString();
    return returnObject;
}
function convertToOblic(lat, lng, zoom, heading) {
    var WMProjPoint = WebMercatorProject(lat, lng, zoom);
    var OblWMProjPoint = OblicWebMercator(WMProjPoint.x, WMProjPoint.y, WMProjPoint.z, heading);
    return OblWMProjPoint;
}
function getDelta(minZ, searchZoom, refTileValue) {
    if (searchZoom &amp;lt;= minZ) {
        let diviseur = minZ - searchZoom;
        return refTileValue / Math.pow(2, diviseur);
    } else {
        let diviseur = searchZoom - minZ;
        return refTileValue * Math.pow(2, diviseur);
    }
}
function WebMercatorProject(lat, lon, zoom) {
    let factor = (1 / (2 * Math.PI)) * Math.pow(2, zoom);
    let x = factor * ((lon * (Math.PI / 180)) + Math.PI);
    let y = factor * (Math.PI - Math.log(Math.tan((Math.PI / 4) + ((lat * (Math.PI / 180)) / 2))));
    var returnTiles = new Object();
    returnTiles.x = x;
    returnTiles.y = y;
    returnTiles.z = zoom;
    return returnTiles;
}
function OblicWebMercator(x0, y0, zoom, heading) {
    let width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles = Math.pow(2, zoom);
    let equator_offset_from_edges = width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles / 2;
    let x = x0;
    let y = y0;
    if (heading == 0) { //is_northward
    }
    if (heading == 90) { //is_eastward
        x = y0;
        y = width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles - x0;
    }
    if (heading == 180) { //is_southward
        x = width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles - x0;
        y = width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles - y0;
    }
    if (heading == 270) { //is_westward
        x = width_and_height_of_world_in_tiles - y0;
        y = x0;
    }
    y = ((y - equator_offset_from_edges) / Math.sqrt(2)) + equator_offset_from_edges
    var returnTiles = new Object();
    returnTiles.x = Math.floor(x).toString();
    returnTiles.y = Math.floor(y).toString();
    returnTiles.z = zoom;
    returnTiles.heading = heading.toString();
    return returnTiles;
}
